						<summary>

						<p>Kāmēśvara temple, central shrine, south base of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">••• ••• Year 7.</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers a royal order assigning the bull-calves (<hi rend="italic">chē</hi>) to be yielded by the cows of the royal pen every year as follows: </p>						

						<p>Ten of the (bull) calves will be released as <hi rend="italic">ṛishabhas.</hi></p>						

						<p>The rest will be utilised for the repairs and maintenances of the construction of the compound wall called Poṉparappiṉa-perumāḷ-tiru-madiḷ, of the temple of Tirukkāmīśvaram-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār.</p>						

						<p>The order was signed by Vāṇakōvaraiyaṉ and Villavarāyaṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
